# ---- Duodecimal HALF ADDER ----
# A + B mod 12, with carry into the next dozenal position.
# When a Sumerian merchant adds 7 sheep + 8 sheep,
# he gets 3 sheep carry 1 dozen. That's this gate.
# (7 + 8 = 15 = 1×12 + 3)
#
# The carry ripples through dozens → grosses (144) →
# great grosses (1728). The positional number system
# that Babylon invented before anyone else.

cell HADD radix 12 inputs 2 outputs 2
  pin A in
  pin B in
  pin S out
  pin C out
  truth  0  0 ->  0 0
  truth  0  1 ->  1 0
  truth  0  2 ->  2 0
  truth  0  3 ->  3 0
  truth  0  4 ->  4 0
  truth  0  5 ->  5 0
