# ---- Duodecimal DFF: stores one dozenal digit ----
# A register that holds values 0-11. One clock edge,
# one dozen possibilities. Like a sundial frozen in time.
# Shamash approves.

cell DFF radix 12 inputs 1 outputs 1
  pin D in
  pin Q out D
  truth  0 ->  0
  truth  1 ->  1
  truth  2 ->  2
  truth  3 ->  3
  truth  4 ->  4
  truth  5 ->  5
  truth  6 ->  6
  truth  7 ->  7
  truth  8 ->  8
  truth  9 ->  9
  truth 10 -> 10
  truth 11 -> 11
end

# ---- Duodecimal CONST ----

cell CONST radix 12 inputs 0 outputs 1
  pin Y out
  truth ->  0
  truth ->  1
  truth ->  2
  truth ->  3
  truth ->  4
  truth ->  5
  truth ->  6
  truth ->  7
  truth ->  8
  truth ->  9
  truth -> 10
  truth -> 11
end

# ---- Duodecimal CONSENSUS: agreement over 12 values ----
# If two scribes read the same cuneiform and agree, output
# their reading. If they disagree, output 0 (unresolved).
# The editorial method, in silicon.
#
# Historical application: if Nanni says the copper is grade 3
# and Ea-nasir ALSO says the copper is grade 3, then fine,
# it's grade 3. But if Nanni says 3 and Ea-nasir says 9,
# the output is 0 (unresolved) because Ea-nasir is a known
# liar about copper quality and the consensus gate correctly
# refuses to propagate disputed metallurgical claims.
#
# This is arguably the world's oldest quality control circuit.

cell CONSENSUS radix 12 inputs 2 outputs 1
  pin A in
  pin B in
  pin Y out cons(A,B)
  truth  0  0 ->  0
  truth  1  1 ->  1
  truth  2  2 ->  2
  truth  3  3 ->  3
  truth  4  4 ->  4
  truth  5  5 ->  5
  truth  6  6 ->  6
  truth  7  7 ->  7
  truth  8  8 ->  8
  truth  9  9 ->  9
  truth 10 10 -> 10
  truth 11 11 -> 11
  truth  0  1 ->  0
  truth  0  2 ->  0
  truth  0  3 ->  0
  truth  0  4 ->  0
  truth  0  5 ->  0
